# Styling Conventions

## CSS Custom Properties (use these, never hardcode colors)
```
--bg-base, --bg-elevated, --bg-surface
--text-primary, --text-secondary, --text-tertiary
--border-default, --border-subtle
--accent, --success, --warning, --danger
```

## Utility Class Naming (defined in index.css)
| Class | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `kpi` | KPI metric card |
| `kpi-label`, `kpi-value`, `kpi-delta` | KPI sub-elements |
| `panel` | Content card / section |
| `panel-title` | Panel heading |
| `panel-action` | Inline link action |
| `grid grid-4` | 4-column responsive grid |
| `grid grid-asym-2` | Asymmetric 2-column (chart + sidebar) |
| `dashboard` | Page wrapper |
| `dash-header`, `dash-title`, `dash-subtitle` | Page header |
| `tbl` | Styled table |
| `badge badge-danger/warning/neutral` | Status badges |
| `dot dot-success/warning/danger` | Status indicator dots |
| `mono` | Monospace text span |
| `burn-grid`, `burn-bar`, `burn-fill` | SLO burn rate bars |
| `dep-row` | Dependency row |

## Tailwind
Tailwind v4 is available but used sparingly — only for layout utilities not covered by the CSS class system above.  
Do NOT use Tailwind for colors or typography; use CSS variables and the existing class system.

## Fonts
- Body/UI: `IBM Plex Sans, sans-serif`
- Monospace/numbers: `IBM Plex Mono, monospace` (class `mono` or inline `fontFamily`)
